    "through different shades of color.",
    "According to the color in the lower-left corner, we ranked the contribution degree from the highest to the lowest.",
    "The color red indicates that the number of papers contributed is more than 300; orange indicates that the number of papers contributed is between 200 and 300; gold indicates that the number of papers contributed is between 100 to 200; green indicates that the number of papers contributed is less than 100; white indicates that the relevant areas have not contributed to TAD research.",
    "It can be seen that China and the United States, followed by Japan, Canada, and some European countries, have made great contributions to temporal action detection research.",
